<h2 id="howtouse">How to use</h2>

<ol>
<li>Log in or sign up by clicking the button in the top right corner of the screen.</li>

<blockquote>
  If you have forgotten your password, click the "Reset your password" button on the login page.
</blockquote>
<li>Once logged in, click the <i>problems</i> tab to see the current list of problems. When you've spotted a problem that you want to attempt, click it to see details.</li>
<li>Once you have clicked a problem you will see a detailed description of the problem, as well as sample test cases at the bottom of the page. On the right side, you will see the problem statistics.</li>
<li>When you feel like you have a working solution to the problem you selected, click the yellow "Submit" button on the right side of the page.</li>
<li>From there, select the language you in which wrote your submission. </li>
<li>You can either upload a file, or "switch to editor" and paste your code there.</li>
<blockquote>If you upload a file and paste code into the editor, the pasted code will be used and the uploaded file will be discarded.</blockquote>
<li>Click "Submit". You will see your program be tested against the test cases for that problem. You will see the results of your submission once it:
<ul>
<li>Completes all test cases</li>

<li>Fails on a test case</li>

<li>Fails to compile</li></ul>
</li>

<li>If not all test cases passed, you can "Submit again", or go "Back to problem" to review the problem. If it did pass all the test cases, <i>Good job!</i></li>
</ol>

