<h2 id="faqs">FAQ's</h2>

<p><em>What does a run-time error mean?</em></p>
<p>It means one of three things:</p>

<ol>
<li>Your program exited with a bad status code.</li>

<li>Your program tried to use system calls that are not allowed.</li>

<li>Your program alloted more memory than what was allowed (1024 MB).</li>
</ol>

<div class="spacer"></div>

<p><em>How are rankings computed?</em></p>
<p>Rankings are scored on two factors. The first one is how many problems you have solved. The more problems you solve, the higher on the leaderboard you will be. The second factor, is the total sum of the amount time each problem took you to solve. This is taken as the difference between the time you submitted your problem and the time the competition started. For example if you submitted 2 problems; One 30 minutes into the competitions, the other 60 minutes into the competition, the total time would be 90 minutes. The lower your total time, the higher on the leaderboard you will be.</p>

